{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9a7d555-6ff3-40cf-95b2-1a71768ffd94","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()` called directly\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is hard to test because you can't easily mock or freeze time in tests.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `timezone.now()` with [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or inject the clock:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis gives you timezone-awareness **and** is easily mockable with `@freeze_time(...)` or `unittest.mock.patch('django.utils.timezone.now')`.\n\n**Summary:** Only 1 file, 1 occurrence found. The project is small — just the single `datetime.now()` call in `views.py`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"058a97ce-e84f-407d-9d70-a635326d746a","outputTokens":221,"requestId":"BC2C:8A8EB:20CBD35:249CE16:69FAA91B"},"id":"136f5a30-f377-49de-92b1-4dff321a95fb","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:36:17.704Z","parentId":"4c7145e6-45cb-485f-b6f9-24e13e885466"}
